dataIdInfo.idPurp: Boundary lines for administrative level 0-3 of Nigeria. Each line is attributed with the highest Admin level that it can represent.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was created by ITOS by converting the Admin2 and 3 layers to lines. The lines were created after all processing on the admin layers had been completed by ITOS.
An 'AdminLevel' field is used to attribute the lines. The values used for this field are: (0,1,2,3,4,5,99). 99 represents coastline. 0 is international border, 1 is Admin1 border, 2 is Admin2 border, etc. Each line is attributed with the highest admin level that it can participate in.
